  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Preheat your oven to 200°C/392°F."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Leaving the skins on, cut the potatoes in half, or into medium chunks if using normal potatoes. Put in a pan of cold salted water, bring to the boil. Once boiling cook for 10 minutes, then drain."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, make the chimichurri. Roughly chop the shallot or red onion and green chilli - removing the seeds if you don’t like it spicy. Put into a mini food processor with the garlic, coriander or parsley (stalks and all), red wine or vinegar, dried oregano, and 100ml olive oil. Blitz to a smooth green sauce. Season to taste and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Peel and slice the chorizo ring. Slice the courgettes into thick diagonal slices. Tip the part boiled potatoes into a large roasting tray along with the chorizo and courgettes. Drizzle over a glug of olive oil, season well with salt and pepper, toss everything together then spread into a single layer. Roast in the oven for 20 minutes whilst you chill."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Scatter the salad leaves over the traybake, drizzle over the chimichurri. Serve at the table for people to help themselves."
    }
  ],
